column1: anna is a noun meaning "gift" in Quenya.
Image:Anna.gifAnna is also the name in Quenya of the twenty-third letter of the Tengwar alphabet.  It is the third letter of the sixth grade or Tyellë
column2: which contains "semi-vocalic" consonants and it is the fifth letter in the third series of consonants.  This letter is commonly used for consonantal Y
column3: except in the Mode of Beleriand.  As seen in the West-gate of Moria inscription
column4: Anna in this "full writing" mode is used for O.  The Westron name for this letter is Yé.See Westron Tengwar

column1: The word derives from the Primitive Quendian Sundocarme ANA.
